g threat to the health, safety, or welfare of all or part of the university community; maintain a daily crime and fire log; among other mandates.         View Annual Security & Fire Safety Report      Other           The Clery Act             Campus Security Authorities (CSA)          Links           Incident Reporting Forms             Annual Report Notification and Availability              PLANNING    Back to main content           Emergency Management     Emergency Operations Plan    Annexes    Emergency Operations Policy Group    Practice Standards      Violence Prevention     Violence Prevention Plan     Behavioral Threat Assessments Teams     BTAT Process    Behavioral Threat Assessment Team for Employees (BTAT-E)    Behavioral Threat Assessment Team for Students (BTAT-S)        Violence Prevention Governance     Members of the Behavioral Threat Assessment Team for  Employees (BTAT-E)    Members of the Behavioral Threat Assessment Team for Students (BTAT-S)      Practice Standards      Clery Compliance     The Clery Act    Campus Security Authorities    Reporting Forms    Clery Governance     Clery Compliance Executive Committee (CCEC)    Clery Compliance Advisory Committee (CCAC)    UI Clery Coordination Council, Regional Committee        Continuity of Operations     University of Illinois Ready      Threat/Hazard Mitigation     Threat and Hazards Identification Risk Assessment    Hazard Mitigation Plan      Training & Exercising     Training Events    Multi-Year Training and Exercise Plan (MYTEP)    Exercises    Emergency Management Institute’s Curriculum     FEMA – Independent Study Courses    FEMA Student Identification Number (FEMA SID)    Incident Command    Continuity of Operations    Campus Seminars      Practice Standards                    UIC Logo        Office of Preparedness and Response         Emergency Response Guidelines    Active Threat/Shooter    Building Evacuation    Extreme Heat    Fire (candles, cooking, smoking)    Shelter-in-Place    